# Commit, push, release automation

## Product goal

When app-impacting changes are pushed to `main`, maintainers expect a **new release entry** (new tag) rather than overwriting artifacts on an old tag. That requires **bumping `versionName`** for each publish.

## Agent obligation (unless explicitly told "WIP/no release")

Before `git commit` (and before any `git push`) that includes app-impacting changes, the agent MUST:

1. Edit `app/build.gradle.kts`:
   - `versionCode`: **+1**
   - `versionName`: bump at least **patch**
2. Add `fastlane/metadata/android/en-US/changelogs/<newVersionCode>.txt` describing the shipped changes (2–10 lines).

## What counts as “app-impacting”

Version bump required when the diff touches e.g.:

- `app/src/**` (Kotlin, resources, manifest, assets)
- `app/build.gradle.kts` or other app module build inputs
- Anything that changes the built APK behavior, metadata, or what users see

Not required when changes are only docs/repo metadata with no APK impact.

## Three remotes

After the commit, push to all three remotes:

- `git push gitlab <branch>`
- `git push github <branch>`
- `git push forgejo <branch>`

